---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Turks and Caicos Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/turks-and-caicos/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Bahamas for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/bahamas' },
  { title: 'Cayman Islands for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/cayman-islands' },
  { title: 'Bermuda for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/bermuda' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'tcisFit', header: 'TCI Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$500-715/mo', tcisFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$585-835/mo', tcisFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$450-645/mo', tcisFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'GeoBlue', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$420-600/mo', tcisFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'NHIP (Local)', entryAge: 'All ages', renewal: 'Required', monthlyFrom: '$200-350/mo', tcisFit: 'Basic' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '$450-715', annual: '$5,400-8,580' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '$615-955', annual: '$7,380-11,460' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '$825-1,280', annual: '$9,900-15,360' },
  { category: 'NHIP (Required)', monthly: '$200-350', annual: '$2,400-4,200' },
  { category: 'Medical Evacuation', monthly: 'N/A', annual: '$30,000-100,000' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Turks and Caicos 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Turks and Caicos. Grace Bay beach, British territory, no income tax, and coverage for wealthy retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Turks and Caicos"
  subheadline="Turks and Caicos offers Grace Bay (world's best beach), British Overseas Territory stability, no income tax, luxury resorts, and easy Miami access—a premium Caribbean destination for wealthy American and British retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/turks-and-caicos-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Turks and Caicos</h2>
  <p>
    Turks and Caicos offers Grace Bay—regularly voted world's best beach, British legal system stability, no income or capital gains tax, luxury resort infrastructure, and just 1.5 hours from Miami. Popular with wealthy American and British retirees seeking Caribbean beauty with familiar systems.
  </p>

  <p>
    Providenciales ("Provo") has most development, Grace Bay, airport, and healthcare. Grand Turk is capital but quieter. Population ~45,000. Miami is 1.5 hours—primary medical backup. British Overseas Territory using US dollar.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Miami 1.5 hours for complex care</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> $4,000-8,000/month (USD); expensive</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round; hurricane zone</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Luxury beach; British; exclusive</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> No income, capital gains, or inheritance tax</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Turks and Caicos Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Healthcare is limited—Cheshire Hall Medical Centre (Provo) and Cockburn Town Medical Centre (Grand Turk) are main facilities. Limited specialists. Most serious cases evacuate to Miami (1.5-hour flight)—very convenient compared to other Caribbean locations. NHIP is mandatory local insurance but limited coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    Miami's Baptist Health, Jackson Memorial, and other facilities provide excellent backup very close by. Many residents maintain Miami doctors for ongoing care. International insurance with US coverage essential.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Miami Is Close</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Miami is just 1.5 hours away—closer than most Caribbean locations. Multiple daily flights. Baptist Health, Jackson Memorial, Mount Sinai Medical Center all accessible. This proximity is major advantage for medical access. Ensure insurance covers US hospitals.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Turks and Caicos residency options (British Overseas Territory):
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residence Certificate (PRC)</h3>
  <p>
    For those investing $300,000+ in real estate or establishing business. Provides indefinite residence rights. Popular option for wealthy retirees.
  </p>

  <h3>Annual Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For those not meeting PRC threshold. Renewable annually. Requires proof of income.
  </p>

  <h3>Belonger Status</h3>
  <p>
    After 10+ years continuous residence. Full rights similar to citizenship.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Turks and Caicos:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>NHIP:</strong> Mandatory local health insurance for residents</li>
    <li><strong>International:</strong> Strongly recommended supplement</li>
    <li><strong>US coverage:</strong> Essential for Miami access</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Important though Miami is close</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for TCI</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      NHIP (mandatory) plus comprehensive international insurance with strong US coverage. Miami proximity is key advantage—ensure seamless US hospital access. Many residents maintain US doctors and fly to Miami for elective care.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Turks and Caicos, US coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for TCI</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong US network, Miami access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>GeoBlue:</strong> US-focused with Caribbean coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Miami proximity:</strong> Quick access to world-class care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for TCI with US hospital access.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Turks and Caicos (USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Total Healthcare Budget</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>NHIP + International:</strong> $650-1,100/month typical</li>
    <li><strong>No income tax:</strong> Offsets healthcare costs</li>
    <li><strong>Miami trips:</strong> Budget for elective care travel</li>
    <li><strong>Premium destination:</strong> Costs match lifestyle</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Beach Lover, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $7,000/month income. Grace Bay condo. Frequent Miami trips.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with full US coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$650/month. Beach paradise; 1.5 hours from Miami doctors.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Retiree, 73</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £6,000/month pension. PRC holder. British legal comfort.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with UK and US coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$800/month. British territory; familiar system; Miami backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Tax Optimizer, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $10,000/month investment income. Tax-free living focus.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with Americas coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~$600/month. Tax savings significant; premium lifestyle.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why choose TCI over Bahamas?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Better beach (Grace Bay consistently ranked higher), smaller/quieter, same tax advantages. Bahamas larger with more services. TCI more exclusive, Bahamas more developed. Both British influenced, both use USD.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is the PRC worth $300,000?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        For long-term residents yes—indefinite residence, no renewals, stable British legal system. Real estate investment can appreciate. For tax savings alone, may not justify cost. Consider lifestyle value.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Hurricane risk in TCI?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate—Hurricanes Irma and Maria (2017) caused significant damage. Proper construction essential. Many residents leave during peak season. Miami is close for evacuation. Building codes improved.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I keep US doctors?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—common practice. Miami is 1.5 hours, many flights daily. Residents maintain US doctors for ongoing care, fly for appointments. International insurance covering US essential. Very practical arrangement.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for TCI coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Local healthcare is limited—US coverage essential. NHIP is mandatory for residents. Always verify current requirements with TCI authorities.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
